cs.GT, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with game theory and network design, which are both topics covered by cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of graphs and optimization techniques suggests that the paper could also fit into cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the study of fairness and social costs could potentially fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
